tech.mcprison.prison.troubleshoot

Class TroubleshootManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • tech.mcprison.prison.troubleshoot.TroubleshootManager

  • public class TroubleshootManager
extends java.lang.Object
    The TroubleshootManager is responsible for containing instances of all registered Troubleshooters. You should register your Troubleshooter here.
    Since:
    API 1.0

      • registerTroubleshooter

        public void registerTroubleshooter(Troubleshooter troubleshooter)
        Register a Troubleshooter with the manager.
        Parameters:
        troubleshooter - The instantiated Troubleshooter to register.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If a Troubleshooter with the same name is already registered.

      • invokeTroubleshooter

        public TroubleshootResult invokeTroubleshooter(java.lang.String name,
                                               CommandSender sender)
        Invoke a specific Troubleshooter.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the Troubleshooter. This is not case sensitive, but should contain underscores.
        sender - The CommandSender invoking this troubleshooter. Messages will be sent to this sender.
        Returns:
        The TroubleshootResult if the Troubleshooter could be run, or null if there is no Troubleshooter by the provided name.
